I am 38 years old and i have three sons. I have been a single parent since 2009. I have now been unemployed for almost two years and taking care of my sons single handedly has been very difficult. I started a small honey business where i would purchase honey from bee keepers in the rural areas and sell it in the city. My main suppliers for the honey were local women's groups and i felt this was a way to support rural women to develop as well. My business was doing well but it collapsed due to lack of capital to maintain and increase stock according to the demand. Also because of my personal situation as a single mum i had to dig in to the business to support my children. 

Because i have been unemployed for a very long time, being able to take care of my children's needs has been virtually impossible. I am mainly concerned about their education and that is the main reason i am asking for this loan. I want to be able to pay for the next two terms to ensure that they are stable in school and then concetrate on building a self sustaining business that will allow me to meet my children's needs as a mother should. 

Please help me with this endevour.
